  "description": [
    "Page Six Havana News False Fire Alarm Causes Excitement The Volunteer Fire Departmeat of Havana was called out on a seemingly false alarm Tuesday morning about 1130 The impression was given that the school was the location of the fire which brought many mothers to see about their children A new stove pipe that was over heated in the home of Ed Shelfer caused the excitement No damage was encountered Demonstration Club Holds Meeting The Home Demonstration Club met Friday afternoon at the home of Mrs C T Tullos with Mrs Hoyt Herring cohostess The theme of the meeting was The Fight against Insects A lecture was given by Miss Elise Laffitte Home Demonstration agent on spraying of plants About 12 were present at the meeting Methodist Youth Entertains The Intermediate department of the Methodist Youth Fellowship of the Salem Methodist Church was entertained with a Valentine Party Monday night at the Com munity House Guests were Intermediates of the other churches Mrs A R Burham Mrs Robert McDavid and Mrs Alvin Stephens were in charge of the entertainment Valentine games were played and refreshments of punch and cookies were served Sixth Grade Gives Assembly Program The Sixth grade of"
